[h2 id=Claiming 
	" Claiming
	$LF
]h2
[div class=p 
	"If you have started working on some submission for publication, notify other publishers you're already encoding it:
	$LF
]div
[ul 
	[li 
		" Edit its text and select 
		[b 
			"Publication Underway
		]b
		" in the movie status drop-down list.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" Add a comment in the text under the horizontal ruler (4 minuses) like:
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[pre 
	"[user:feos]: Processing...
	$LF
]pre
[div class=p 
	"Alternately, hit the Claim button.
	$LF
]div
[hr 
]hr
[h2 id=Publishing 
	" Publishing
	$LF
]h2
[div class=p 
	"After all files are ready, click the 
	[b 
		"Publish
	]b
	" link on the submission page.
	$LF
]div
[ul 
	[li 
		" 
		[b 
			"Always double-check the game names put into submissions. Always apply 
			(__wikiLink|displaytext=our standards|href=/PublisherGuidelines#GameName)
			" to them.
		]b
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[ul 
	[li 
		" Set flags if any of them are appropriate.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" Type the movie file name, taking the name of encodes, just dropping away 
		[b 
			"-tas/-playaround
		]b
		", and putting the author at the beginning:
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[pre 
	"feosv3-battletoadsj-1p
	$LF
]pre
[ul 
	[li 
		" Choose screenshot from your computer
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" Put the direct link to downloadable encode from the Archive.org collection into the 
		[b 
			"mirror site URL
		]b
		" field.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" Put the YouTube HD stream link to the 
		[b 
			"online-watching URL
		]b
		" field.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" For the Description and categories tab, type in the movie number to be obsoleted (if it was decided by the judge), fill the description (1 paragraph about the game, 1 about how it was played in that TAS). If it obsoleted some movie, and the new time is actually shorter, you can calculate the frame difference yourself and manually create the module:
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[pre 
	" This movie beats the [1000M|previous run] by [module:frames|amount=300|fps=ntsc] seconds
	$LF
]pre
[ul 
	[li 
		" If this run has 
		(__wikiLink|displaytext=commentary|href=/Commentaries)
		", add a note about it to the movie description under a ruler 
		[code 
			"--
			[em 
			]em
			"--
		]code
		", telling the user their form, and how to access them.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" Add tags listed by the submission author. Still, don't copy them blindly, some physics-abusing tricks do not mean it is 
		[b 
			"Heavy glitch abuse
		]b
		", the same is with 
		[b 
			"Heavy luck manipulation
		]b
		".
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[div class=p 
	"When you are sure all is done properly, click the Proceed button. Note that the title and description on YouTube will be automatically edited and made public with the description copied over from the movie description. It does not need to be manually edited in the vast majority of cases. The same occurs for adding a new encode or replacing an already existing encode on an already published movie. The replaced encode gets set to unlisted (so that it's no longer searchable on YouTube) with the new encode being set to public.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"For a movie that starts from a save RAM, the verificiation movie needs to be added as an additional movie file. Simply edit the publication, and add the verification movie as an additional movie file, following the same naming convention as the publication movie file, adding 
	[code 
		"-verif
	]code
	" at the end of the verification movie file name. Put 
	[code 
		"Verification movie
	]code
	" as the display name and click on Add.
	$LF
]div
